# Append-heavy content files: when a cloud-agent run races a concurrent push,
# resolve overlapping appends by keeping BOTH sides instead of failing the
# run's final rebase and losing 30-50 minutes of output (Issue #59, second
# failure). Union merge is line-based and applies during rebase as well.
research-log.md merge=union
storage-angle.md merge=union
user-field-notes.md merge=union
playbook.md merge=union
sources.md merge=union
agent-watchlist.md merge=union
daily/*.md merge=union
weekly/*.md merge=union
monthly/*.md merge=union
automation/runs/*.md merge=union
automation/source-health.md merge=union
automation/source-lanes.md merge=union
# NOTE: automation/screening/*.json is deliberately NOT union-merged — line
# union on JSON yields invalid JSON; those files are write-once per day and
# effectively never conflict.
